Etymology[edit]

From prae +‎ audiō.

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /prae̯ˈau̯.di.oː/, [prae̯ˈau̯.d̪i.oː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /preˈau̯.di.o/, [prɛˈau̯.d̪i.ɔ]

Verb[edit]

praeaudiō (present infinitive praeaudīre, perfect active praeaudīvī or praeaudiī, supine praeaudītum); fourth conjugation

  1. I hear beforehand
